2026-06-24 01:49:05,660 DEBUG msg #118: UserMessage tool_result(toolu_01DtSJnJcEWrxS29gKG1xivp): 1	# World Cup 2026 Prediction — Competitive Live Forecast (Groll RF Hybrid)
2	
3	## Description
4	A Python CLI that produces a **live, in-tournament probabilistic forecast** of the FIFA World Cup
5	2026 winner — full title odds for every nation plus round-by-round advancement probabilities. The
6	goal is **accuracy-first**: match or beat the bookmaker baseline (measured by RPS / log-loss / Brier).
7	It replaces the current SVM/RandomForest/NaiveBayes win/loss classifier (data-biased, European-only
8	artifact) with a **Groll-style Random-Forest hybrid** that uses time-weighted Dixon-Coles/Poisson team
9	abilities + Elo as covariates, trained on full national-team history. WC2026 is **mid-group-stage**, so
10	the forecast conditions on results played to date and simulates the remaining groups → knockout.
11	
12	## Tech Stack
13	<!-- The tool uses this information to select the right agents -->
14	- **Language**: Python 3.11+
15	- **Framework**: Typer CLI + Pydantic config (library; **no web UI**)
16	- **Database**: none (CSV / JSON artifacts on disk)
17	- **Deploy**: local CLI (`worldcup-playoff`), hatchling build
18	- **Tests**: pytest (250 existing tests must stay green)
19	- **Core libs**: numpy, pandas, scikit-learn, **statsmodels** (Poisson), scipy, fitter, matplotlib,
20	  requests, **beautifulsoup4/lxml** (odds + Elo scraping)
21	- **Modeling**: Dixon-Coles / bivariate Poisson abilities → Random-Forest / gradient-boosting hybrid
22	  (Groll-Ley-Zeileis style), Elo ordered-logit as a secondary/baseline
23	
24	## Key Decisions (locked with the user)
25	- **Purpose:** real competitive forecast — beat the bookies.
26	- **Model:** full Groll RF hybrid (Poisson abilities + Elo as RF covariates).
27	- **Covariates:** **football-only** — NO socio-economic / market-value / GDP. NO yfinance.
28	- **Bookmaker odds:** **NOT a model feature.** Used only as the **backtest baseline** to beat.
29	- **Output:** full title odds (every team) + round-by-round advancement.
30	- **Sim start:** WC2026 is in progress (Round of 16 not yet reached) → **use all data to date**:
31	  fold in played group results, simulate remaining group fixtures → Round of 32 → knockout.
32	- **Data:** martj42 (no-key history, all nations) **+** football-data.org (live WC2026).
33	- **Deliverable:** CLI + PNG outputs (as today).
34	
35	## Features
36	<!-- List the features. Each entry becomes a GitHub Issue -->
37	1. **No-key historical loader (martj42).** `data/martj42_loader.py` — fetch CC0
38	   `martj42/international_results` `results.csv` (cols `date, home_team, away_team, home_score,
39	   away_score, tournament, city, country, neutral`; coerce `"NA"` scores → nullable, `"TRUE"/"FALSE"` →
40	   bool) plus `shootouts.csv` and `goalscorers.csv`. Map into the internal `matches.csv` schema
41	   (`DATE, HOME_TEAM, AWAY_TEAM, HOME_GOALS, AWAY_GOALS, TOURNAMENT, NEUTRAL`). Every nation gets real
42	   history, and the file already includes the WC2026 schedule. Default training source (zero auth).
43	   See **Data Contracts** for exact shapes.
44	2. **Live WC2026 adapter (football-data.org).** `data/live.py` — pull current WC2026 standings,
45	   played results, and **remaining group fixtures** via the existing `FootballClient` (key in `.env`).
46	   Normalize team names to match martj42. Provide "state of tournament as of today".
47	3. **Elo engine.** `data/elo.py` — compute World Football Elo from match history (k-factor × margin ×
48	   match importance) or ingest eloratings.net; emit per-team, per-date Elo + Elo-difference. Seed the
49	   live state from history so WC2026 teams enter with current ratings.
50	4. **Dixon-Coles ability estimator.** `simulation/poisson.py` — independent/bivariate Poisson with
51	   attack & defence strengths, home advantage, `rho` low-score correction, **exponential time-decay**.
52	   Fit on martj42; expose per-team attack/defence abilities as model covariates and as a standalone
53	   scoreline sampler.
54	5. **Football-only feature builder.** `features/build.py` — assemble per-match covariates: Elo,
55	   Elo-diff, FIFA ranking, time-weighted recent form, goal difference, Dixon-Coles attack/defence
56	   abilities, rest days, confederation, **neutral-venue flag**. All no-key.
57	6. **Groll RF hybrid model.** `models/hybrid.py` — Random-Forest / gradient-boosting regressor-or-
58	   classifier that consumes the Poisson abilities + Elo + covariates to predict per-match goals (or
59	   W/D/L distribution). This is the primary predictor. Keep `models/ordered_logit.py` (Elo-diff
60	   ordered logit) as a strong secondary, and the legacy SVM/RF/NB only as a backtest baseline.
61	7. **Live tournament simulator.** Extend `simulation/tournament.py` to: (a) ingest played WC2026
62	   results as fixed, (b) simulate **remaining group matches** with correct FIFA group + tiebreak
63	   rules to resolve the Round of 32, (c) simulate the knockout (draw → extra time `λ×0.33` → penalty
64	   coin-flip), (d) run ~**100,000** Monte Carlo tournaments → **full title odds + per-round
65	   advancement** for all 48 teams.
66	8. **Historical odds scraper (backtest baseline).** `data/odds.py` — scrape archived WC2014/2018/2022
67	   outright + match odds (de-vig to probabilities). Robust to source changes; cache to CSV. Used only
68	   for evaluation, never as a feature.
69	9. **Evaluation + backtest.** `models/evaluation.py` — **RPS (primary), log-loss, Brier** on
70	   **time-aware** (no-shuffle) splits; backtest the hybrid on WC2014/2018/2022 and report metrics
71	   **vs the scraped bookmaker baseline** and vs the legacy classifier. Success = ≈ or beat bookies.
72	10. **Config + CLI surface.** Add `[poisson]`, `[elo]`, `[rf]`, `[odds]`, `[live]` config sections
73	    (Pydantic + TOML). CLI commands: `fetch-live`, `build-features`, `train-hybrid`, `backtest`,
74	    `forecast` (live title odds), plus existing `bracket`/PNG rendering. Keep 250 tests green and add
75	    tests for every new module.
76	
77	## Non-functional Requirements
78	<!-- Performance, security, scalability, accessibility -->
79	- **Accuracy is the acceptance criterion:** hybrid RPS ≈ or below the bookmaker baseline on backtests.
80	- **No-key default:** training/forecast must run without any API key (martj42 + computed Elo). The
81	  football-data.org key is optional, only for live WC2026 state; stored in `.env` (gitignored — the
82	  repo is public, never commit secrets).
83	- **Live re-runnable:** `forecast` can be re-run after each matchday to update odds as results land.
84	- **Reproducibility:** deterministic given a seed; no nondeterministic fitting that breaks replays.
85	- **Validation rigor:** time-aware splits only; never shuffle chronological data; report probabilistic
86	  metrics (RPS/log-loss/Brier), not raw accuracy.
87	- **Performance:** ~100k Monte Carlo tournaments complete in seconds–low minutes.
88	- **Resilience:** odds/Elo scrapers degrade gracefully (cache + fallback) so a blocked source never
89	  breaks the forecast.
90	- **Backward compatibility:** keep the Typer command surface, PNG outputs, and the existing test suite.
