Random Forest regressors average the values in their leaf nodes, so adding those 6 away-win examples would shift the home goal prediction from 3.0 down to 2.4 by changing how the tree splits. Rather than relying on an arbitrary threshold like 0.9, I'll use a more robust assertion: checking that `prob_home > prob_away` holds true regardless of whether the model trains on just the home wins or includes both datasets.

