2026-06-24 03:03:50,863 DEBUG msg #260: assistant (tool_use) tool_use(Write): {'file_path': '/Volumes/External SSD/worldcup-2026-prediction/tests/test_models_no_key_smoke.py', 'content': '"""\nSource-blind example tests for Issue #15:\n    feat: models package no-key integration smoke test (hybrid + ordered logit + baseline)\n\nCriteria covered (from oracle report — only UNIT-verifiable items):\n  [UNIT] Criterion 1  — end-to-end pipeline: martj42 fixture → compute_elo →\n                        fit_dixon_coles → build_features → build_dataset → model.fit\n  [UNIT] Criterion 4  — re-fitting both models with the same seed yields identical predictions\n  [UNIT] Criterion 5  — ClassifierFactory.create still builds svm/random_forest/naive_bayes\n  [UNIT] Criterion 6  — worldcup_playoff.models re-exports Cycle-4 surface + legacy exports\n\nCriteria skipped (oracle: NOT VERIFIABLE):\n  - Hybrid predicted goals >= 0 and W/D/L probs sum to 1\n  - Ordered-logit W/D/L probs sum to 1\n  - All tests pass (meta-gate, not a per-criterion assertion)\n  - SOLID / code-quality prose\n\nNo implementation files were read when authoring this module (Red phase of TDD).\nAll behaviour is derived solely from the acceptance-criteria text and requirements.md.\n"""\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom hypothesis import given, settings\nfrom hypothesis import strategies as st\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Shared fixture factory (no network access; martj42 column schema)\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n_TEAMS = [\n    "Brazil", "Argentina", "France", "Germany",\n    "Spain", "England", "Italy", "Portugal",\n]\n\n_DATES = [\n    "2018-06-14", "2018-06-15", "2018-06-16", "2018-06-17",\n    "2018-06-18", "2018-06-19", "2018-06-20", "2018-06-21",\n    "2022-11-20", "2022-11-21", "2022-11-22", "2022-11-23",\n    "2022-11-24", "2022-11-25", "2022-11-26", "2022-11-27",\n    "2026-06-11", "2026-06-12", "2026-06-13", "2026-06-14",\n    "2026-06-15", "2026-06-16", "2026-06-17", "2026-06-18",\n    "2026-06-19", "2026-06-20", "2026-06-21", "2026-06-22",\n    "2026-06-23", "2026-06-24",\n]\n\n\ndef _martj42_fixture(n_rows: int = 30) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    """\n    Minimal martj42-schema DataFrame for offline tests.\n\n    Columns: date, home_team, away_team, home_score, away_score,\n             tournament, city, country, neutral.\n    home_team != away_team by construction ((i%8) != ((i+1)%8) for all i).\n    """\n    rows = [\n        {\n            "date": _DATES[i % len(_DATES)],\n            "home_team": _TEAMS[i % len(_TEAMS)],\n            "away_team": _TEAMS[(i + 1) % len(_TEAMS)],\n            "home_score": i % 4,\n            "away_score": i % 3,\n            "tournament": "FIFA World Cup" if i % 5 == 0 else "Friendly",\n            "city": "City",\n            "country": "United States",\n            "neutral": i % 3 == 0,\n        }\n        for i in range(n_rows)\n    ]\n    df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n    df["date"] = pd.to_datetime(df["date"])\n    return df.sort_values("date").reset_index(drop=True)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Criterion 1 — no-key end-to-end pipeline  [UNIT]\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef test_when_martj42_fixture_is_piped_through_full_pipeline_then_hybrid_model_is_fitted():\n    """\n    Criterion 1: compute_elo → fit_dixon_coles → build_features → build_dataset\n    → HybridModel.fit succeeds and .predict returns one label per sample.\n\n    Assumption: each pipeline function returns its output which is forwarded to\n    the next stage; HybridModel is sklearn-compatible (fit/predict).\n    """\n    from worldcup_playoff.data.elo import compute_elo\n    from worldcup_playoff.features.build import build_features\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.dataset import build_dataset\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.hybrid import HybridModel\n    from worldcup_playoff.simulation.poisson import fit_dixon_coles\n\n    matches = _martj42_fixture()\n    elo = compute_elo(matches)\n    dc = fit_dixon_coles(matches)\n    features = build_features(matches, elo, dc)\n    X, y = build_dataset(features)\n\n    model = HybridModel(random_state=0)\n    model.fit(X, y)\n\n    assert len(model.predict(X)) == len(y)\n\n\ndef test_when_martj42_fixture_is_piped_through_full_pipeline_then_ordered_logit_model_is_fitted():\n    """\n    Criterion 1 (continued): the same pipeline feeds OrderedLogitModel successfully.\n\n    Assumption: OrderedLogitModel is sklearn-compatible (fit/predict).\n    """\n    from worldcup_playoff.data.elo import compute_elo\n    from worldcup_playoff.features.build import build_features\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.dataset import build_dataset\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.ordered_logit import OrderedLogitModel\n    from worldcup_playoff.simulation.poisson import fit_dixon_coles\n\n    matches = _martj42_fixture()\n    elo = compute_elo(matches)\n    dc = fit_dixon_coles(matches)\n    features = build_features(matches, elo, dc)\n    X, y = build_dataset(features)\n\n    model = OrderedLogitModel()\n    model.fit(X, y)\n\n    assert len(model.predict(X)) == len(y)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Criterion 4 — determinism  [UNIT + property]\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef test_when_hybrid_model_is_refit_with_same_seed_then_predictions_are_identical():\n    """Criterion 4: identical seed → identical HybridModel predictions on the same data."""\n    from worldcup_playoff.data.elo import compute_elo\n    from worldcup_playoff.features.build import build_features\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.dataset import build_dataset\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.hybrid import HybridModel\n    from worldcup_playoff.simulation.poisson import fit_dixon_coles\n\n    matches = _martj42_fixture()\n    elo = compute_elo(matches)\n    dc = fit_dixon_coles(matches)\n    X, y = build_dataset(build_features(matches, elo, dc))\n\n    m1 = HybridModel(random_state=42)\n    m1.fit(X, y)\n\n    m2 = HybridModel(random_state=42)\n    m2.fit(X, y)\n\n    np.testing.assert_array_equal(m1.predict(X), m2.predict(X))\n\n\ndef test_when_ordered_logit_model_is_refit_with_same_data_then_predictions_are_identical():\n    """Criterion 4: OrderedLogitModel is deterministic — re-fitting yields identical predictions."""\n    from worldcup_playoff.data.elo import compute_elo\n    from worldcup_playoff.features.build import build_features\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.dataset import build_dataset\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.ordered_logit import OrderedLogitModel\n    from worldcup_playoff.simulation.poisson import fit_dixon_coles\n\n    matches = _martj42_fixture()\n    elo = compute_elo(matches)\n    dc = fit_dixon_coles(matches)\n    X, y = build_dataset(build_features(matches, elo, dc))\n\n    m1 = OrderedLogitModel()\n    m1.fit(X, y)\n\n    m2 = OrderedLogitModel()\n    m2.fit(X, y)\n\n    np.testing.assert_array_equal(m1.predict(X), m2.predict(X))\n\n\n@given(st.integers(min_value=0, max_value=9999))\n@settings(max_examples=10, deadline=None)\ndef test_when_hybrid_is_refit_with_any_seed_then_output_is_reproducible(seed):\n    """\n    Criterion 4 (property / invariant): for every random seed in the integer domain,\n    fitting HybridModel twice with that same seed always returns identical predictions.\n    Determinism is unconditional — it must hold across all valid seed values.\n    """\n    from worldcup_playoff.data.elo import compute_elo\n    from worldcup_playoff.features.build import build_features\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.dataset import build_dataset\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.hybrid import HybridModel\n    from worldcup_playoff.simulation.poisson import fit_dixon_coles\n\n    matches = _martj42_fixture()\n    elo = compute_elo(matches)\n    dc = fit_dixon_coles(matches)\n    X, y = build_dataset(build_features(matches, elo, dc))\n\n    m1 = HybridModel(random_state=seed)\n    m1.fit(X, y)\n\n    m2 = HybridModel(random_state=seed)\n    m2.fit(X, y)\n\n    np.testing.assert_array_equal(m1.predict(X), m2.predict(X))\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Criterion 5 — ClassifierFactory baseline coexistence  [UNIT + property]\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef test_when_classifier_factory_creates_svm_then_a_classifier_is_returned():\n    """Criterion 5: ClassifierFactory.create(\'svm\') still returns a non-None baseline object."""\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.classifiers import ClassifierFactory\n\n    assert ClassifierFactory.create("svm") is not None\n\n\ndef test_when_classifier_factory_creates_random_forest_then_a_classifier_is_returned():\n    """Criterion 5: ClassifierFactory.create(\'random_forest\') still returns a baseline object."""\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.classifiers import ClassifierFactory\n\n    assert ClassifierFactory.create("random_forest") is not None\n\n\ndef test_when_classifier_factory_creates_naive_bayes_then_a_classifier_is_returned():\n    """Criterion 5: ClassifierFactory.create(\'naive_bayes\') still returns a baseline object."""\n    from worldcup_playoff.models.classifiers import ClassifierFactory\n\n    assert ClassifierFactory.create("naive_bayes") is not None\n\n\n@given(st.sampled_from(["svm", "random_forest", "naive_bayes"]))\ndef test_when_any_baseline_name_is_passed_to_factory_then_sklearn_protocol_is_satisfied(name):\n    """\n    Criterion 5 (property / invariant): for every valid baseline name, the object\n    returned by ClassifierFactory.create satisfies the sklearn Protocol — .fit and\n    .predict are present. The invariant holds for the entire set of baseline names.\n    """\n    from worldcup_