h `compute_elo` → `fit_dixon_coles` → `build_features` → `build_dataset`.\n- [ ] Hybrid output: predicted goals `>= 0` and W/D/L probabilities sum to 1.\n- [ ] Ordered-logit output: W/D/L probabilities sum to 1.\n- [ ] Re-fitting both models with the same seed yields identical predictions (determinism).\n- [ ] `ClassifierFactory.create` still builds the `svm`/`random_forest`/`naive_bayes` baselines (baseline coexistence).\n- [ ] `worldcup_playoff.models` re-exports the full Cycle-4 surface alongside the legacy exports.\n- [ ] The full existing suite stays green (`pytest`).\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #13: feat: Groll-style RF/GBM goal-based hybrid model (primary predictor)\n- #14: feat: Elo-diff ordered logit secondary model (statsmodels)\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `tests/test_models_integration.py` — build a small in-memory/fixture martj42 results frame, run the full no-key path, and assert the criteria above. Reuse fixture patterns from `tests/test_features_build.py` and `tests/conftest.py`; keep each test focused (one behavior per test).\n- **Verify (modify only if a gap remains):** `worldcup_playoff/models/__init__.py` exposes `HybridGoalModel`, `GoalPrediction`, `fit_hybrid`, `OrderedLogitModel`, `OutcomeProbabilities`, `fit_ordered_logit`, `MatchDataset`, `build_dataset` plus the legacy `ClassifierFactory`/`ClassifierTrainer`/`ModelEvaluator`.\n- Run `pytest` to confirm the existing 711 tests remain green after the additive Cycle-4 modules land.\n- No new CLI commands, no Monte-Carlo simulation, no scoring/backtest harness, no odds — those are Cycle 5.\n- Conventions: deterministic seeds, mypy strict, ruff line-length 100.","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIFtA","name":"priority:medium","description":"Medium priority","color":"FBCA04"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopII0g","name":"phase:implement","description":"Phase: implement","color